{{Nihongo|'''Yuki Tanaka'''|田中 利幸|Tanaka Toshiyuki|extra=born May 26, 1949}} is a History Professor at [[Hiroshima University]]. He has written extensively about [[Comfort women|forced prostitution]] under the [[Japanese Empire]], as well as in [[Japan under US military rule]]. He also writes about the [[laws of warfare]].
==Works== * ''Hidden Horrors: Japanese War Crimes in World War II'', Westview Press (1996) ISBN 0-8133-2718-0 * ''Japan's Comfort Women: Sexual Slavery and Prostitution During World War II and the US Occupation'', Routledge (2001) ISBN 0-415-19401-6 * (co-edited with [[Marilyn B. Young]]) ''Bombing Civilians: A Twentieth Century History'', The New Press (2009) ISBN 1-59558-363-7
==External links== * "Introducing Yuki TANAKA" [http://japanfocus.org/-Yuki-TANAKA Personal information in Japan Focus website] * [https://web.archive.org/web/20091121160809/http://www.counterpunch.org/tanaka05262005.html "Firebombing and Atom Bombing"], [[CounterPunch]], May 26, 2005 * [https://web.archive.org/web/20090608081900/http://www.wagingpeace.org/articles/2005/01/25_tanaka_hibakusha-voice.htm "The Hibakusha Voice and the Future of the Anti-Nuclear Movement"], lecture delivered on January 25, 2005 * "Japan admits war crimes conducted in WWII" [http://www.abc.net.au/lateline/stories/s661377.htm Transcript of an interview with Prof. Tanaka] on Australian Broadcasting Corporation, broadcast August 28, 2002 * {{YouTube|wmg8p0meU5c|Yuki Tanaka on the Hiroshima peace movement (video)}} * [http://www.digital-development-debates.org/issue-15-responsibility--responsibility-for-the-future--a-proposal-from-hiroshima.html A Proposal from Hiroshima], article by Yuki Tanaka in Digital Development Debates, July 2015.
